name: Remix
description: Remix IDE is a web-based Integrated Development Environment (IDE) for writing, compiling, deploying, and debugging Solidity smart contracts on the Ethereum blockchain. It offers developers a comprehensive suite of tools to efficiently create and interact with decentralized applications (dApps) directly from their browser.

name: Buildspace
description: Buildspace is an educational Web3 platform that allows users to build sample Web3 projects. The projects come in a variety of lengths and difficulties. The platform places you in a "cohort" with other people working on the same project as you , in a discord server. This allows for debugging help, sharing progress, and general support through the process.

name: Etherscan
description: Built in 2015 by Block Solutions Sdn Bhd, Etherscan is an Ethereum block explorer and analytics platform. Users can see and analyze assets, balances and transactions on the Ethereum network. Developers can interact with smart contracts and view gas prices on Etherscan. Etherscan is one of the most trusted and popular block explorers for Ethereum.

name: MetaMask
description: A free, digital cryptocurrency wallet that allows users to store and manage their cryptocurrencies, interact with decentralized applications (dApps), and execute transactions on blockchain networks.

name: Rabby
description: a non-custodial cryptocurrency wallet that supports many blockchains, including Ethereum and related Ethereum Virtual Machine (EVM) blockchains.

name: Rainbow Kit
description: a free, open-source React library that helps developers add wallet connections to their web3 frontends and improve their products

name: The Graph
description: The Graph (GRT) is a decentralized, open-source protocol that indexes and queries data from blockchains like Ethereum and Avalanche.

name: Alchemy
description: The leading web3 blockchain developer platform. Supercharge your dApps with the most reliable and scalable development endpoints in just one magic line of code.

name: Chainlink
description: a cryptocurrency and technology platform that allows non-blockchain businesses to connect with blockchain platforms in a secure way.

name: Open Zeppelin
description: A crypto cybersecurity company that provides an open-source framework for building secure smart contracts

name: Ethers.js
description: A JavaScript library for interacting with the Ethereum blockchain and its ecosystem. Itâ€™s lightweight and focuses on simplicity and security.

name: web3.js
description: A widely-used JavaScript library for interacting with Ethereum nodes via HTTP, IPC, or WebSocket connections.

name: Infura
description: A service that provides scalable and reliable access to Ethereum and IPFS networks. It's commonly used to interact with blockchain networks without running a full node.

name: Hardhat Network
description: An Ethereum development environment that includes a local network with advanced features like Solidity stack traces and console.log support.

name: Moralis
description: Provides a full-stack Web3 development platform with tools for authentication, real-time database, and blockchain interactions.

name: Ceramic
description: Decentralized data at scale. Ceramic powers an ecosystem of interoperable apps and services running on verifiable, scalable data infrastructure.

name: Pinata
description: Pinata makes it simple to store and retrieve media on IPFS. Quickly build apps, collaborate with others, and analyze insights about your IPFS files.

name: Ganache
description: Quickly fire up a personal Ethereum blockchain which you can use to run tests, execute commands, and inspect state while controlling how the chain operates.
